{
  "title": "Documenting Serverless Handlers with FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This explainer provides a guide on how to document serverless functions using the FastAPI framework when programming in Python 3.12+.",
  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI supports automatic documentation generation for APIs in Python.",
    "To document serverless handlers, you'll need the `fastapi-serverless` library in addition to `fastapi` and `uvicorn`.",
    "The `@pydantic_model` decorator can be applied to your handler classes for enhanced documentation.",
    "Use `@APIRouter` from FastAPI instead of `FastAPI` as the base class for serverless handlers.",
    "Set up AWS Lambda or other serverless platform configurations following their specific guides."
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "from fastapi import FastAPI\nfrom fastapi.router import APIRouter\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\n\nclass Item(BaseModel):\n    name: str\n    description: str\n    price: float\n\nrouter = APIRouter()\n@router.get('/items/{item_id}')\ndef get_item(item_id: int, item: Item = None):\n    ...\napp = FastAPI()\napp.include_router(router)\n"
    },
    {
      "language": "yaml",
      "code": "handler: main\nruntime: python3.12\nenvironment:\n  paths:\n    - /path/to/your/project\n    - /usr/local/lib/\n    - /var/task\n  variables:\n    APPLICATION_ID: my-application\n    AWS_REGION: us-west-2\ndependencies:\n  - requirements.txt"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12 is required to run the examples.",
    "Ensure you have the latest versions of `fastapi`, `uvicorn`, and `fastapi-serverless` installed."
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "The example provided does not include actual AWS Lambda or other serverless platform configurations.",
    "Remember to replace the example paths with your own project's directories."
  ]
}
